Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA March 10 -- Foreign Minister Nguyen Manh 
Cam today held talks at the government guest house with visiting 
Dutch Foreign Minister Peter Kooijmans. 
  During the talks F.M. Nguyen Manh Cam informed his Dutch 
counterpart of Vietnam's current situation and initial 
achievements in the renovation process. He highlighted the 
recently important changes for the better in the relations 
between Vietnam and other countries in the region and in other 
parts of the world. Mr. Cam expressed his wish for the further 
development of the friendship and cooperation between Vietnam 
and the Netherlands. 
  For his part. P.M. Kooijmans spoke highly of Vietnam's 
results in its renovation process and open-door policy. He said 
he believed that his visit would mark an important step in the 
development of the friendship and cooperation in various fields 
between Vietnam and the Netherlands. The two ministers also 
exchanged views on international issues of common concern. 
  Also in this morning the two foreign ministers signed an 
agreement on investment encouragement and protection between 
Vietnam and the Netherlands. 
  Present at the signing ceremony were deputy head of the 
State 
Commission for Cooperation and Investment Nguyen Nhac, and Dutch 
Ambassador to Vietnam Mr. D. Ader. 

